description.narrative: (Georgia): .The Georgia Primary Education Project (G-PriEd) provides comprehensive assistance to the primary education system in Georgia to improve reading and math competencies and develop business skills of Georgian and ethnic minority students. G-PriEd supports up to 560 public schools in improving methods of instructions. Activities include increasing the availability of language- and age-appropriate reading and math materials; enhancing testing and classroom assessment tools; promoting the use of new technologies; and engaging parents and communities in the instructional process. G-PriEd will allow the target schools to provide continuous training and in-service support to 8,000 teachers; improve reading and math competencies of 40,000 primary grade students; support reading and math clubs with parents' engagement; and expand the current reach of the program to additional 1,000 students to promote a school-based acquisition of business skills among learners at primary grades..
